HEADWORD: Direption
<hw>Di*rep"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>direptio</ets>, fr. <ets>diripere</ets> to tear asunder, plunder;
<ets>di- = dis-</ets> + <ets>rapere</ets> to seize and carry off.]</ety>
<def>The act of plundering, despoiling, or snatching away.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Speed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Direptitious</ent>⟦br⟧
